# SlotSync — Privacy Policy

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

SlotSync is a Chrome extension that helps you find mutually free time with colleagues and schedule meetings. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data collection

SlotSync does **not** collect, store, transmit or share any personal data with third parties.

## How it works

- You sign in with your Google account using OAuth2
- SlotSync queries Google's Calendar Freebusy API to check when you and your colleagues are free — it receives only free/busy blocks, not the titles or details of individual events
- Meeting events are created directly in your Google Calendar via the Calendar API
- Contact suggestions are fetched from your Google Contacts and your organisation's directory
- Your Zoom personal room URL (if saved) is stored locally in `chrome.storage.local` and never leaves your device
- No data is sent to any external server other than Google's own APIs

## Permissions

| Permission | Reason |
|---|---|
| `identity` | To authenticate with Google via OAuth2 |
| `storage` | To store your Zoom URL and OAuth token locally |
| `sidePanel` | To display SlotSync as a browser side panel |

## Google API access

SlotSync requests the following Google OAuth scopes:

| Scope | Reason |
|---|---|
| `calendar.readonly` | To read your own calendar for availability checking |
| `calendar.events` | To create new meeting events in your calendar |
| `calendar.freebusy` | To check free/busy blocks for you and colleagues |
| `contacts.readonly` | To suggest colleagues from your personal contacts |
| `directory.readonly` | To suggest colleagues from your organisation's directory |

## Revoking access

Sign out at any time using the Sign out button. To fully revoke access, visit [myaccount.google.com/permissions](https://myaccount.google.com/permissions) and remove SlotSync.

